quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  6,127,"They will have the Home of Peace with their Lord, Who will be their Guardian because of what they used to do"
  6,128,"ňĻConsiderňļ the Day He will gather them ňĻallňļ together and say, ‚ÄúO assembly of jinn! You misled humans in great numbers.‚ÄĚ And their human associates will say, ‚ÄúOur Lord! We benefited from each other‚Äôs company,¬†but now we have reached the term which You appointed for us.‚ÄĚ ňĻThenňļ He will say, ‚ÄúThe Fire is your home, yours to stay in forever, except whoever Allah wills to spare.‚ÄĚ¬†Surely your Lord is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,129,This is how We make the wrongdoers ňĻdestructiveňļ allies of one another because of their misdeeds
  6,130,"ňĻAllah will ask,ňļ ‚ÄúO assembly of jinn and humans! Did messengers not come from among you, proclaiming My revelations and warning you of the coming of this Day of yours?‚ÄĚ They will say, ‚ÄúWe confess against ourselves!‚ÄĚ For they have been deluded by ňĻtheirňļ worldly life. And they will testify against themselves that they were disbelievers"
  6,131,This ňĻsending of the messengersňļ is because your Lord would never destroy a society for their wrongdoing while its people are unaware ňĻof the truthňļ
  6,132,They will each be assigned ranks according to their deeds. And your Lord is not unaware of what they do
  6,133,"Your Lord is the Self-Sufficient, Full of Mercy. If He wills, He can do away with you and replace you with whoever He wills, just as He produced you from the offspring of other people"
  6,134,"Indeed, what you have been promised will certainly come to pass. And you will have no escape"
  6,135,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO my people! Persist in your ways, for I ňĻtooňļ will persist in mine. You will soon know who will fare best in the end. Indeed, the wrongdoers will never succeed.‚ÄĚ"
  6,136,"The pagans set aside for Allah a share of the crops and cattle He created, saying, ‚ÄúThis ňĻportionňļ is for Allah,‚ÄĚ so they claim, ‚Äúand this ňĻoneňļ for our associate-gods.‚ÄĚ Yet the portion of their associate-gods is not shared with Allah while Allah‚Äôs portion is shared with their associate-gods. What unfair judgment"
  6,137,"Likewise, the pagans‚Äô evil associates have made it appealing to them to kill their own children‚ÄĒonly leading to their destruction as well as confusion in their faith. Had it been Allah‚Äôs Will, they would not have done such a thing. So leave them and their falsehood"
  6,138,"They say, ‚ÄúThese cattle and crops are reserved‚ÄĒnone may eat them except those we permit,‚ÄĚ so they claim. Some other cattle are exempted from labour and others are not slaughtered in Allah‚Äôs Name‚ÄĒfalsely attributing lies to Him. He will repay them for their lies"
  6,139,"They ňĻalsoňļ say, ‚ÄúThe offspring of this cattle is reserved for our males and forbidden to our females; but if it is stillborn, they may all share it.‚ÄĚ He will repay them for their falsehood. Surely He is All-Wise, All-Knowing"
  6,140,Lost indeed are those who have murdered their own children foolishly out of ignorance and have forbidden what Allah has provided for them‚ÄĒfalsely attributing lies to Allah. They have certainly strayed and are not ňĻrightlyňļ guided